Here is a simple jQuery script that will hide all HTML elements that have a class of "hide-this":

```javascript
$(document).ready(function(){ 
  $(".hide-this").hide(); 
});
```

This script first waits for the document to be ready, then selects all elements with the "hide-this" class by using the `$(".hide-this")` selector. We then call the `hide()` method on these elements, which hides them on the page.

